        Search3 looks for user input in the records and returns a true or false boolean value to determine whether the user input is valid or not.
        Parameters:
        fileName - The name of the external file which contains the record.
        data - The two-dimensional array that stores the records.
        item - Specifies the list to be sorted by names, ids, homeforms or periods.
        input - The input is the String entered by the user
        input2 - The input2 is the String entered by user for the movie.
        Returns:
        z The boolean indicates whether the input was successfully found (true) or not (false).
